    "To mitigate this, it's advisable for the model to discard external references and rely on its intrinsic knowledge.",
    "We achieve this by altering the question-answering prompt, guiding the model to rely solely on its internal knowledge.",
    "• Only External Knowledge Available.",
    "Conversely, in situations where only external knowledge is present, LLMs can be prone to hallucinations if they mistakenly believe they know the answer.",
    "To circumvent this, we ask the LLM to only rely on the provided references for its response.Erroneous Reasoning."
